--- Lemmings Budget Hard Disk Installer ---

This installer requires the ORIGINAL disk(s) from Lemmings,Lemmings Budget or
Oh No More Lemmings.

It will NOT work for cracked versions.

The HD-Patched game will need about 1.5Mb of memory for the 1 disk version and
3.5Mb for the 2 disk version, but you can use the HDLOAD tooltype to reduce
memory consumption.


FEATURES:

- Runs fully from RAM/HD
- 8 versions supported.
- Works using JOTDStartup (jst), included in the archive.
- Convenient installer script
- Can be run either in PAL or NTSC (country check removed)
- All versions run on a standard A1200/020/NoFast
- F10 quits the game
- Disk, code checksum and password protection removed (hard work)
- TRAINER tooltype gives infinite time

SUPPORTED VERSIONS:

- Lemmings Original PAL (2 versions, one with screen centered vertically)
- Lemmings Original NTSC
- Oh No More Lemmings NTSC
- Oh No More Lemmings NTSC (trackdos disk version)
- Oh No More Lemmings PAL (with password or disk protection)
- Lemmings Budget PAL

If somebody has got Lemmings CD32, Lemmings Budget NTSC,
or any other unsupported version, please let me know.


INSTALLING THE GAME:

Just run the installer script relevant to your version.
The installers will install different games in different directories so you can
install all the versions at a time.

If you did not install JST before, copy it in your path (better in C:)

The installer also checks that you inserted the correct disk. In case of problem
during the installation, you can partially re-install the game by hand using
the rippsyfiles command.

After that you just have to adjust the tooltypes and start the game by clicking on
the LemmingsHD icon or by typing LemmingsHD <options> in a shell.

