BUGS & COMMENTS:

I had several bug reports from users of the loader who used the Budget version, and
the 2 disked version of the original levels game.

When you entered a level code over level 7, it crashed or showed white stripes.
This is now *REALLY* fixed. There were also blocker bugs, sprite bugs...
I found 2 very nasty code checksum routines and I removed them, so now the game works
fine (I tried to enter level codes up to level 10 and it works).

Thanks for notifying me about the different problems. This one was really strongly and
cleverly protected!!
I'm not that clever but I stroke the final blow on this f***ing protection
(not hard to cleanup in Oh No More Lemmings versions).

There are some minor bugs in the intro animation (2 disk version) but not in the latest
version. It works fine from floppy, and I can't figure out why this happens.
Not serious anyway.

This install really meant hard work, because of the strong protection, and also
because of the several different versions that exist.

If you want to register JST only for this one, you can :)


